etsysPimExtMIB.name: etsysPimExtMIB

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB module

etsysPimExtMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsysPimExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP MIB under the Enterasys Networks enterprise OID pertaining to the PIM configuration. This MIB was designed to be used in conjunction with the PIM-MIB (RFC 5060) for configuring the PIM protocol parameters. Additional statistical tables are provided for monitoring the PIM protocol.

etsysPimExtIfTable.name: etsysPimExtIfTable
etsysPimExtIfTable.description: This table provides additional information pertaining to PIM interfaces for Enterasys PIM systems. This table augments the pimInterfaceTable from RFC 5060.

etsysPimExtIfEntry.name: etsysPimExtIfEntry
etsysPimExtIfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtIfTable.

etsysPimExtIfAdminStatus.name: etsysPimExtIfAdminStatus
etsysPimExtIfAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of PIM on this interface. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusDown', no PIM messages will be sent or received on this interface. The TIB state pertaining to this interface is cleared, resulting in the removal of the associated routes from the MFIB. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusUp', normal PIM operation will proceed, and multicast state is stored in the TIB when it is learned.

etsysPimExtIfOperStatus.name: etsysPimExtIfOperStatus
etsysPimExtIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of PIM on this interface.

etsysPimExtIfP2PNoHellos.name: etsysPimExtIfP2PNoHellos
etsysPimExtIfP2PNoHellos.description: Indicates whether this interface is a point-to-point interface. If the value of this object is 'true', neighbors are not required to send PIM-Hello messages. This is provided for backward-compatibility with some older implementations that do not send PIM-Hellos on point-to-point links. Changing the value of this object while the interface is operationally active MAY cause the interface to be deactivated and then reactivated.

etsysPimExtIfNeighborCount.name: etsysPimExtIfNeighborCount
etsysPimExtIfNeighborCount.description: The number of PIM neighbors on this interface.

etsysPimExtIfStarGStateLimit.name: etsysPimExtIfStarGStateLimit
etsysPimExtIfStarGStateLimit.description: The maximum number of groups for which the PIM TIB Manager is allowed to store (*,G,I) state specific to this interface. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysPimExtIfStarGStateWarnThold.name: etsysPimExtIfStarGStateWarnThold
etsysPimExtIfStarGStateWarnThold.description: The PIM TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of groups for which it is storing (*,G,I) state specific to this interface exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysPimExtIfStarGStateStored.name: etsysPimExtIfStarGStateStored
etsysPimExtIfStarGStateStored.description: The number of groups for which the PIM TIB Manager is storing (*,G,I) state specific to this interface.

etsysPimExtIfSGStateLimit.name: etsysPimExtIfSGStateLimit
etsysPimExtIfSGStateLimit.description: The maximum number of {source, group} pairs for which the PIM TIB Manager is allowed to store (S,G,I) state specific to this interface. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysPimExtIfSGStateWarnThold.name: etsysPimExtIfSGStateWarnThold
etsysPimExtIfSGStateWarnThold.description: The PIM TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of {source, group} pairs for which it is storing (S,G,I) state specific to this interface exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysPimExtIfSGStateStored.name: etsysPimExtIfSGStateStored
etsysPimExtIfSGStateStored.description: The number of {source, group} pairs for which the PIM TIB Manager is storing (S,G,I) state specific to this interface.

etsysPimExtIfAssertInterval.name: etsysPimExtIfAssertInterval
etsysPimExtIfAssertInterval.description: The frequency at which this router sends PIM Assert messages on this interface when it is the assert winner. This object corresponds to the 'Assert_Time' (180 seconds) minus the 'Assert_Override_Interval' (3 seconds) defined in PIM-SM [RFC 4601]. This value MUST be less than etsysPimExtIfAssertHoldtime.

etsysPimExtIfAssertHoldtime.name: etsysPimExtIfAssertHoldtime
etsysPimExtIfAssertHoldtime.description: The interval before this router leaves assert loser state on this interface, unless it receives a PIM Assert message that refreshes this state. This object corresponds to the 'Assert_Time' timer value defined in PIM-SM [RFC 4601]. Note: Configuring different values for this object for different routers on the same interface may lead to incorrect protocol operation.

etsysPimExtStaticRPTable.name: etsysPimExtStaticRPTable
etsysPimExtStaticRPTable.description: This table provides additional information pertaining to PIM static rendezvous points for Enterasys PIM systems. This table augments the pimStaticRPTable from RFC 5060.

etsysPimExtStaticRPEntry.name: etsysPimExtStaticRPEntry
etsysPimExtStaticRPEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtStaticRPTable.

etsysPimExtStaticRPAdminStatus.name: etsysPimExtStaticRPAdminStatus
etsysPimExtStaticRPAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of this entry. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusDown', the static rendezvous point will no longer accept PIM messages and is removed from the pimGroupMappingTable. This MAY cause the TIB to be updated. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusUp', this static rendezvous point is added to the pimGroupMappingTable and will start accepting PIM messages. This MAY cause the TIB to be updated.

etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetTable.name: etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetTable
etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetTable.description: This table provides additional information pertaining to PIM anycast rendezvous point sets for Enterasys PIM systems. This table augments the pimAnycastRPSetTable from RFC 5060.

etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetEntry.name: etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetEntry
etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetTable.

etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetAdminStatus.name: etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetAdminStatus
etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of this entry. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusDown', the router is removed from the corresponding anycast rendezvous point set. This MAY cause the TIB to be updated. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusUp', the router is added to the anycast rendezvous point and will start handling PIM messages. This MAY cause the TIB to be updated. Note: If the status is set to 'adminStatusDown' and the pimAnycastRPSetLocalRouter object is 'true' (this entry corresponds to the local router), the entire set is invalidated. The Anycast-RP Set is only valid if the local router is a member of the set.

etsysPimExtGroupMappingTable.name: etsysPimExtGroupMappingTable
etsysPimExtGroupMappingTable.description: This table provides additional information pertaining to PIM group mapping for Enterasys PIM systems. This table augments the pimGroupMappingTable from RFC 5060.

etsysPimExtGroupMappingEntry.name: etsysPimExtGroupMappingEntry
etsysPimExtGroupMappingEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtGroupMappingTable.

etsysPimExtGroupMappingIsInactive.name: etsysPimExtGroupMappingIsInactive
etsysPimExtGroupMappingIsInactive.description: Indicates whether this Group Mapping is currently inactive. If this flag is set to 'true' then this group mapping is currently not in use. In other words, no group addresses will be matched to this Group Mapping.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsTable.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsTable
etsysPimExtNbrStatsTable.description: This table provides additional information pertaining to PIM neighbor statistics for Enterasys PIM systems. This table augments the pimNeighborTable. Note: If a Neighbor expires and is removed from the pimNeighborTable and is reconnected shortly thereafter, these statistics are reset due to the row deletion. The statistics MAY also reset on receipt of a PIM Hello message with a zero holdtime.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsEntry.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsEntry
etsysPimExtNbrStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtNbrStatsTable.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvHello.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvHello
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvHello.description: The number of valid PIM Hello messages that have been received from this neighbor.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvJoinPrune.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvJoinPrune
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvJoinPrune.description: The number of valid PIM Join/Prune messages that have been received from this neighbor.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvAssert.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvAssert
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvAssert.description: The number of valid PIM Assert messages that have been received from this neighbor.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvBSM.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvBSM
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumRecvBSM.description: The number of valid PIM Bootstrap messages that have been received from this neighbor.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrJoinPrune.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrJoinPrune
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrJoinPrune.description: The number of PIM Join/Prune messages that have been received from this neighbor that have contained errors. Note: This does not include messages for which the RP in the message differs from the RP known by the local router, nor does it include (*,G) messages received for SSM groups.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrAssert.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrAssert
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrAssert.description: The number of PIM Assert messages that have been received from this neighbor that have contained errors.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrBSM.name: etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrBSM
etsysPimExtNbrStatsNumErrBSM.description: The number of PIM Bootstrap messages that have been received from this neighbor that have contained errors.

etsysPimExtIfStatsTable.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsTable
etsysPimExtIfStatsTable.description: This table provides additional information pertaining to PIM interface statistics for Enterasys PIM systems. This table augments the pimInterfaceTable.

etsysPimExtIfStatsEntry.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsEntry
etsysPimExtIfStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtIfStatsTable.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentHello.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentHello
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentHello.description: The number of PIM Hello messages that have been sent out this interface.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentJoinPrune.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentJoinPrune
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentJoinPrune.description: The number of PIM Join/Prune messages that have been sent out this interface.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentAssert.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentAssert
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentAssert.description: The number of PIM Assert messages that have been sent out this interface.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentBsm.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentBsm
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumSentBsm.description: The number of PIM Bootstrap Router messages that have been sent out this interface. PIM always multicasts this type of message.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumErrHello.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumErrHello
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumErrHello.description: The number of PIM Hello messages that have been received on this interface that have contained errors.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumRecvUnknownNbr.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumRecvUnknownNbr
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumRecvUnknownNbr.description: The number of PIM Join/Prune, Assert and multicast Bootstrap Router messages that have been received on this interface from a neighbor in which we had not previously received a valid PIM Hello message (and for which etsysPimExtIfP2PNoHellos was 'false'). Bootstrap Router messages which are sent to a unicast address are not included in this count.

etsysPimExtIfStatsNumUnknownHelloOpt.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsNumUnknownHelloOpt
etsysPimExtIfStatsNumUnknownHelloOpt.description: The number of unknown options that have been received in PIM Hello messages on this interface.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrTable.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrTable
etsysPimExtNbrMgrTable.description: This table provides objects that manipulate the operation of PIM in order to accept additional types of messages. Statistical objects are provided as well.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrEntry.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrEntry
etsysPimExtNbrMgrEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtNbrMgrTable.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrIndex.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrIndex
etsysPimExtNbrMgrIndex.description: The Internet address version of this Neighbor Manager.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrEnableUnicastMessages.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrEnableUnicastMessages
etsysPimExtNbrMgrEnableUnicastMessages.description: Indicates whether the PIM Neighbor Manager sends and receives unicast PIM messages. This object MUST only be set to 'false' if the local router will never be an RP for any multicast group, and it will never be the downstream router for any connected source that sends data to any ASM group. This will always be the case if the local router only performs the SSM subset of PIM-SM.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrAcceptUnicastBsms.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrAcceptUnicastBsms
etsysPimExtNbrMgrAcceptUnicastBsms.description: Indicates whether the PIM Neighbor manager accepts PIM Boostrap Messages (BSMs) which are sent as unicast messages. Setting the value of this object to 'false' means that BSMs are ignored if they are sent as unicast messages. This object can only be set to 'true' if the etsysPimExtNbrMgrEnableUnicastMessages object is 'true'.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentCRPAdvert.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentCRPAdvert
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentCRPAdvert.description: The number of PIM Candidate-RP-Advertisement messages that have been sent.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentRegister.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentRegister
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentRegister.description: The number of PIM Register messages that have been sent Note: This only includes PIM Register messages forwarded to other members of Anycast-RP sets, and Null-Register messages. It does not include Register-encapsulated data packets sent from the downstream router to the RP.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentRegisterStop.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentRegisterStop
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumSentRegisterStop.description: The number of PIM Register-Stop messages that have been sent.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvCRPAdvert.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvCRPAdvert
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvCRPAdvert.description: The number of valid PIM Candidate-RP Advertisement messages that have been received.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvRegister.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvRegister
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvRegister.description: The number of valid PIM Register messages that have been received.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvRegisterStop.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvRegisterStop
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvRegisterStop.description: The number of valid PIM Register-Stop messages that have been received.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrCRPAdvert.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrCRPAdvert
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrCRPAdvert.description: The number of received PIM Candidate-RP Advertisement messages that have contained errors.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrRegister.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrRegister
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrRegister.description: The number of received PIM Register messages that have contained errors.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrRegisterStop.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrRegisterStop
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumErrRegisterStop.description: The number of received PIM Register-Stop messages that have contained errors.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvIgnoredType.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvIgnoredType
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvIgnoredType.description: The number of received PIM messages with a known but unsupported PIM message type.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvUnknownType.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvUnknownType
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvUnknownType.description: The number of received PIM messages with an unknown PIM message type.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvUnknownVer.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvUnknownVer
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvUnknownVer.description: The number of received PIM messages with an unknown PIM version.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvBadChecksum.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvBadChecksum
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvBadChecksum.description: The number of received PIM messages with an incorrect PIM checksum that.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvBadLength.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvBadLength
etsysPimExtNbrMgrNumRecvBadLength.description: The number of received PIM messages with a length too short to contain a common PIM header.

etsysPimExtTibMgrTable.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrTable
etsysPimExtTibMgrTable.description: This table provides objects that manipulate the operation of the PIM Tree Information Base (TIB) Manager in order control the acceptable limits for the TIB.

etsysPimExtTibMgrEntry.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrEntry
etsysPimExtTibMgrEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysPimExtTibMgrTable.

etsysPimExtTibMgrIndex.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrIndex
etsysPimExtTibMgrIndex.description: The Internet address version of this PIM TIB Manager.

etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateLimit.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateLimit
etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateLimit.description: The maximum number of groups for which the PIM TIB Manager is allowed to store non-interface specific (*,G) and/or (S,G) state. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateWarnThold.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateWarnThold
etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateWarnThold.description: The PIM TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of groups for which it is storing non-interface specific (*,G) and/or (S,G) state exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateStored.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateStored
etsysPimExtTibMgrGStateStored.description: The number of groups for which the PIM TIB Manager is storing non-interface specific (*,G) and/or (S,G) state.

etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateLimit.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateLimit
etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateLimit.description: The maximum number of {source, group} pairs for which the PIM TIB Manager is allowed to store non-interface specific (S,G) state. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateWarnThold.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateWarnThold
etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateWarnThold.description: The PIM TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of {source, group} pairs for which it is storing non-interface specific (S,G) state exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateStored.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateStored
etsysPimExtTibMgrSGStateStored.description: The number of {source, group} pairs for which the PIM TIB Manager is storing non-interface specific (S,G) state.

etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateLimit.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateLimit
etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateLimit.description: The maximum number of {group, interface} pairs for which the PIM TIB Manager is allowed to store (*,G,I) state. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateWarnThold.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateWarnThold
etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateWarnThold.description: The PIM TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of {group, interface} pairs for which it is storing (*,G,I) state exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateStored.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateStored
etsysPimExtTibMgrStarGIStateStored.description: The number of {group, interface} pairs for which the PIM TIB Manager is storing (*,G,I) state.

etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateLimit.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateLimit
etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateLimit.description: The maximum number of {source, group, interface} triplets for which the PIM TIB Manager is allowed to store (S,G,I) state. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateWarnThold.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateWarnThold
etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateWarnThold.description: The PIM TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of {source, group, interface} triplets for which it is storing (S,G,I) state exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateStored.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateStored
etsysPimExtTibMgrSGIStateStored.description: The number of {source, group, interface} triplets for which the PIM TIB Manager is storing (S,G,I) state.

etsysPimExtTibMgrRegSuppressionTime.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrRegSuppressionTime
etsysPimExtTibMgrRegSuppressionTime.description: The mean value of the randomized interval during which a downstream router stops Register-encapsulation after receiving a PIM Register-Stop message. This object corresponds to the 'Register_Suppression_Time' defined in PIM-SM [RFC 4601]. Note: Configuring different values for this object for different routers in the PIM domain may lead to incorrect protocol operation.

etsysPimExtTibMgrRegProbeTime.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrRegProbeTime
etsysPimExtTibMgrRegProbeTime.description: The time to wait for a PIM Register-Stop message after sending a PIM Null-Register message, before resuming Register-encapsulation at a downstream router. This object corresponds to the 'Register_Probe_Time' defined in PIM-SM [RFC 4601].

etsysPimExtTibMgrKeepalivePeriod.name: etsysPimExtTibMgrKeepalivePeriod
etsysPimExtTibMgrKeepalivePeriod.description: The amount of time to keep (S,G) state alive in the absence of PIM (S,G) Join messages, (S,G) local membership or (S,G) data packets. This object corresponds to the 'Keepalive_Period' defined in PIM-SM [RFC 4601]. Note: Configuring different values for this object for different routers in the PIM domain may lead to incorrect protocol operation.

etsysPimExtIfGroup.name: etsysPimExtIfGroup
etsysPimExtIfGroup.description: This group defines interface controls for Enterasys PIM systems.

etsysPimExtStaticRPGroup.name: etsysPimExtStaticRPGroup

etsysPimExtAnycastRPSetGroup.description: This group defines the anycast rendezvous point controls for Enterasys PIM systems.

etsysPimExtGroupMappingGroup.description: This group defines the group mapping controls for Enterasys PIM systems.

etsysPimExtNbrStatsGroup.description: This group defines the neighbor statistic objects for Enterasys PIM systems.

etsysPimExtIfStatsGroup.name: etsysPimExtIfStatsGroup
etsysPimExtIfStatsGroup.description: This group defines the interface statistic objects for Enterasys PIM systems.

etsysPimExtNbrMgrGroup.name: etsysPimExtNbrMgrGroup
etsysPimExtNbrMgrGroup.description: This group defines the neighbor manager objects for Enterasys PIM systems.

etsysPimExtTibMgrGroup.description: This group defines the Tree Information Base (TIB) manager objects for Enterasys PIM systems.
